## Documentation Usage Guidelines

1. **Version-Specific Documentation:**
   - Always reference documentation for the exact versions used in this project
   - Angular 19: Use angular.dev (not angular.io)
   - Bootstrap 5.3.2: Use getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/
   - ng-bootstrap 18.0.0: Use ng-bootstrap.github.io

2. **Primary Reference Priority:**
   - First: Official Angular 19 documentation (angular.dev)
   - Second: Official Bootstrap 5.3.2 documentation (getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/)
   - Third: Official ng-bootstrap 18.0.0 documentation (ng-bootstrap.github.io)

3. **When Searching for Solutions:**
   - Always check version-specific documentation first
   - Verify that examples and code snippets are compatible with the project's versions
   - Prefer official documentation over third-party tutorials or blog posts

4. **API Reference:**
   - For Angular APIs: Use https://angular.dev/reference
   - For Bootstrap classes and utilities: Use https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/utilities/
   - For ng-bootstrap components: Use https://ng-bootstrap.github.io/#/components

5. **Migration and Breaking Changes:**
   - Check Angular 19 migration guide for breaking changes from previous versions
   - Verify Bootstrap 5.3.2 compatibility with any Bootstrap features used
   - Review ng-bootstrap 18.0.0 changelog for component-specific changes

